                    <p><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> @Model.Date?.ToString("d MMM yyyy")</p>
                    @* <p>@ViewBag.TWNews.NewsSummary</p> *@
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="latest-bikes-details-content">
                <h3 class="subheading">Top 5 Royal Enfield Bikes in India (2025 Edition)</h3>
                <p>@Html.Raw(@Model.BlogSummary.Replace("\n", "<br>"))</p>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading"><a class="for-link" asp-controller="RoyalEnfield" asp-action="REClassic350">1. Royal Enfield Classic 350</a></h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/may/top5royalenfieldbikesinindia/reclassic350.png" alt="bikecarhubreclassic350" title="bikecarhubreclassic350" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>The <span class="text-highlight">Royal Enfield Classic 350</span> remains a quintessential choice for riders seeking a blend of heritage and contemporary performance. Equipped with a <span class="text-highlight">349.34cc</span> air-cooled engine, it delivers approximately <span class="text-highlight">20.2 bhp</span> and <span class="text-highlight">27 Nm</span> of torque. Its retro design, combined with modern features like dual-channel ABS and a semi-digital instrument cluster, offers a nostalgic yet practical riding experience. The Classic 350 is available in multiple variants, with ex-showroom prices ranging from<span class="text-highlight"> ₹1.93 lakh to ₹2.25 lakh</span></p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Specification & Features</h5>
				<ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine Type:</span> 349.34 cc, air-cooled engine</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Mileage:</span> 41.5 kmpl</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Max Power:</span> 20.21 PS@6100 rpm</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Fuel Capacity:</span> 13 L</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Max Torque:</span> 27 Nm@4000 rpm</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading"><a class="for-link" asp-controller="RoyalEnfield" asp-action="REHunter350">2. Royal Enfield Hunter 350</a></h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/may/top5royalenfieldbikesinindia/rehunter350.webp" alt="bikecarhubrehunter350" title="bikecarhubrehunter350" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>Targeting urban riders, the <span class="text-highlight">Hunter 350</span> is Royal Enfield's most affordable offering, starting at <span class="text-highlight">₹1.50 lakh</span> (ex-showroom). Powered by the same <span class="text-highlight">349.34cc engine</span> as the Classic 350, it produces around <span class="text-highlight">20.4 bhp and 27 Nm of torque.</span> Its lightweight design and agile handling make it ideal for city commuting, while its modern-retro styling appeals to younger audiences.</p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Specification & Features</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine Type: </span>349.34 cc, Single cylinder, 4 stroke, SOHC Engine</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Mileage: </span>36.2 kmpl</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Max Power:</span> 20.4 PS@6100 rpm</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Fuel Capacity:</span> 13 L</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Max Torque:</span> 27 Nm@4000 rpm</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading"><a class="for-link" asp-controller="RoyalEnfield" asp-action="REBullet350">3. Royal Enfield Bullet 350</a></h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/may/top5royalenfieldbikesinindia/rebullet350.webp" alt="bikecarhubrebullet350" title="bikecarhubrebullet350" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>An icon in its own right, the<span class="text-highlight"> Bullet 350 </span>carries forward Royal Enfield's legacy with its timeless design and characteristic thump. The 2025 model features the updated <span class="text-highlight">349cc engine,</span> ensuring smoother performance and compliance with current emission norms. Priced between <span class="text-highlight">₹1.74 lakh and ₹2.16 lakh</span> (ex-showroom), the Bullet 350 continues to be a favorite among purists.</p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Specification & Features</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine Type: </span>349 cc, Single cylinder, 4 stroke, Air-Oil cooled</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Mileage:</span> 37 kmpl</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Max Power:</span> 20.4 PS@6100 rpm</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Fuel Capacity:</span> 13 L</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Max Torque: </span>27 Nm@4000 rpm</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading"><a class="for-link" asp-controller="RoyalEnfield" asp-action="REMeteor350">4. Royal Enfield Meteor 350</a></h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/may/top5royalenfieldbikesinindia/remeteor350.webp" alt="bikecarhubremeteor350" title="bikecarhubremeteor350" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>For those inclined towards cruising, the <span class="text-highlight">Meteor 350 </span>offers a comfortable ride with its relaxed ergonomics and long wheelbase. It houses the <span class="text-highlight">349cc engine, </span>delivering about <span class="text-highlight">20.4 bhp and 27 Nm of torque.</span>Features like the Tripper navigation system and a comfortable seat make it suitable for long-distance touring. The Meteor 350 is priced between ₹2.06 lakh and ₹2.30 lakh (ex-showroom). </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Specification & Features</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine Type:</span> 349 cc, Single cylinder, 4 stroke, Air-Oil cooled</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Mileage:</span> 41.88 kmpl</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Max Power:</span> 20.4 PS@6100 rpm</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Fuel Capacity:</span> 15 L</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Max Torque:</span> 27Nm@4000 rpm</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading"><a class="for-link" asp-controller="RoyalEnfield" asp-action="REHimalyan">5. Royal Enfield Himalayan 450</a></h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/may/top5royalenfieldbikesinindia/rehimalayan450.webp" alt="bikecarhubrehimalayan450" title="bikecarhubrehimalayan450" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>Catering to adventure enthusiasts, the <span class="text-highlight">Himalayan 450 </span>is built to tackle diverse terrains. It boasts a <span class="text-highlight">452cc engine,</span> producing approximately <span class="text-highlight">39.5 bhp and 40 Nm</span> of torque, offering enhanced performance over its predecessor. With features like switchable ABS, long-travel suspension, and a robust frame, it's designed for both on-road comfort and off-road prowess. The Himalayan 450 is priced between <span class="text-highlight">₹2.85 lakh and ₹2.98 lakh</span> (ex-showroom). </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Specification & Features</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine Type:</span> 452 cc, Liquid Cooled, Single Cylinder, 4 Valves, DOHC</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Mileage: </span>30 kmpl</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Max Power: </span>40.02 PS@8000 rpm</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Fuel Capacity:</span> 17 L</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Max Torque:</span> 40 Nm@5500 rpm</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
